story.text: I am in love with Montana. There is genuinely no place better that I have been. The people are friendly, rough, real, and ready. Though I will struggle to prove myself as a true Montanan, I am sure that I will succeed. Today is my first day of work at the Axilon Law Group, PLLC. I am excited for the road ahead. I plan to spend three days a week in Billings, at first, then less and less as time goes on and I establish my own practice in Red Lodge and Nye. (Red Lodge is where I will spend the rest of my time in Winter, and Nye in Summer.)
The plan is to join the RL fire department, buy real estate there, thoroughly ingrain myself into the community, and then organize a future for the community that will please everyone.
One thing of particular interest is the creation of a startup community.
